modules.description: Parses Content-Type values according to RFC822 and RFC2045, extracting media type, subtype, and parameters. It handles structured data like media ranges and parameter lists, supporting exact and wildcard matching. Use it to validate HTTP headers, analyze MIME types, or process email content with precise type definitions.

Provides functions to parse, print, and construct MIME content types, including media type, subtype, parameters, and full content structures. Works with types such as `ty`, `subty`, `value`, `content`, and `error` to represent and manipulate RFC2045 content headers. Used to validate and serialize HTTP content types, extract parameters from headers, and handle default text/plain parsing.
